article.headline: South Florida 63, Winston-Salem 43
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) -- McHugh Mattis finished with 22 points, 10 rebounds and 10 blocked shots to record the second triple-double in South Florida history and help the Bulls defeat Winston-Salem 63-43 on Thursday. Solomon Bozeman added 17 points and went 3-for-6 on 3-pointers for the Bulls (5-1). Jamal Durham and Darius Floyd scored 10 points each to lead Winston-Salem (1-11), which led 22-21 at the half after forcing 14 South Florida turnovers. The Rams widened the lead to six points with 13:13 remaining before Mattis dunked and sparked a 19-0 run for the Bulls. Winston-Salem has now lost eight straight.
